<center>[[Level 10.1]], named as '''"Transitional Surrealism"''', is the first sublevel of [[Level 10]].</center>
== <Div class="b">Description</div> ==
{{Underline|964B00}}
{{Audio|round=yes|file=If you need me I'll be in the snow - gakhed.mp3|align=center|loop=true|volume=0.1}}
{{Blurimage|file=Surreal Transit.png|align=right|caption=The emptiness through the field.}}
{{Blurimage|file=Surreal transit3.jpg|align=right|caption=Furnished modern building.}}
{{Blurimage|file=Surreal transit4.png|align=right|caption=Isolated pond within the blank plain.}}
[[Level 10.1]] is a boundless grassland, brightly illuminated in spite of its jet-black sky. The ankle-height tufts are a mix of amber and earthy brown, with a soft orange glow. When stepped on or touched, the grass instantly darkens to almost black and stiffens in place for a few seconds before returning to its natural state. Wanderers usually describe the sensation as the ground "blinking." The nature and purpose of this responsiveness remains unknown.

[[Level 10.1]] features an unnatural plant growth of supernaturally long, and straight trees evenly planted across the terrain. These trees stretch indefinitely into the black sky, therefore their tops are unseen. Despite their tremendous height, the trees are completely rigid and unresponsive to wind nor other physical contact.

Its foliage of higher regions are composed of thin, and dark-green leaves blending into the dark sky. When these leaves are disturbed by physical contact, the contacted leaves instantly brighten to a deep amber glow. This interaction also causes the surrounding air temperature to lower sharply to around 3°C, with frost occasionally forming nearby. After several seconds, the glow abates, the temperature returns to normal, and the leaves stiffen again.

Scattered rarely across [[Level 10.1]] are small, perpetually clean, and modern residential structures. These buildings appear in two distinct architectural styles: one is grayscale and minimalist, with minimal external features, and the other is colored in brown and appears plain on the exterior, but has fully furnished and maintained interior. Both designs are consistent in their interiors, usually containing evenly arranged beds and air-conditioning furnitures that are functional in spite of no visible power source. Paradoxically, each structure emits a subtle, and calming chime ambience throughout the interior, although no source has been found. The chime stops immediately upon leaving the building.

Occasionally, the continuous grassy terrain is interrupted by rivers and ponds. These bodies of water feature surfaces that reflect a distinctly different sky: one with white clouds and flocks of birds never seen in the outer surrounding environment. Diving into these waters shows strange, and non-Euclidean depths, appearing as canyon-like voids that stretch indefinitely, with no measurable bottom despite attempts at exploration.

Bridges featuring a clean, and modern architecture span these rivers and ponds, usually found ignoring scale or logic. Physical interaction with the wooden planks of the bridges causes a brief, heightened contrast in the grain and texture of the wood, which fades back to normal after a few seconds.

{{Blurimage|file=Surreal transit6.png|align=right|caption=Four stars within the dark sky, orbiting the sublevel.}}
Prolonged staying within the residential structures of [[Level 10.1]]<ref>Usually the time about three to five minutes.</ref> have been connected to the appearance of a unique celestial phenomenon. Luminous, star-shaped objects emerge in the black sky, usually along the northern and southern horizons. These objects flicker in color: between dark brown and bright amber in cycles that may last about three minutes each. Closer focus revealed the color changing encodes patterns that align with Morse code. Decoding these signals yields fragmented, cryptic messages such as:
<div style="border-left: 1px solid tan; padding: 5px; margin: -1em 1em 0.5em 5em;"> › The pain of being watched<br> › False static everyone sees<br> › Time is eating away<br> › Cycle can or may reset or restart in seconds </div>
These messages suggest [[Level 10.1]] may be watching or manipulating the inhabitants of the itself. The movements of the celestial bodies mimic the sun and moon of [[The Frontrooms]], producing an artificial day-night cycle that influences stamina, energy, and focus. During the "evening" phase, smaller crescent-shaped orbs appear, arranged in constellations that also appear to be constantly flicker colors in Morse-like patterns. Decoded phrases include:
<div style="border-left: 1px solid tan; padding: 5px; margin: -1em 1em 0.5em 5em;"> › Why leave it does not matter there are no exits<br> › Gaze at the sky with patience<br> › Do not stare you may hear<br> › The mysteries cannot be solved this way </div>
Exposure to these celestial patterns<ref>Especially for those individuals who repeated decoding.</ref> has been found out to be associated with headaches, visual distortions, short-term memory issues, and a strange sense of predictive insight. The cause of these phenomena are unknown, with theories ranging from a built-in control mechanism of the level to an external method of communication. Research into the patterns, their variability, and their psychological effects is ongoing.

