== <div class="b">Additional Informations</div> ==
{{Underline|964B00}}
The sky of [[Level 10.1]], despite appearing as a featureless void of pitch-black, reveals the true nature of it under direct illumination. When a flashlight or any focused light source is aimed upward, the darkness reacts unnaturally, revealing a solid surface, just beyond reach. Upon contact with the light beam, this surface flickers with subtle, advanced RGB grid patterns, like the pixel format of a malfunctioning screen or a digital device stuck in mid-refresh. The colors form no coherent image, but instead pulse and rearrange in scattered clusters, suggesting that the sky is not sky at all, but a constructed barrier, perhaps a projection screen or containment dome. As the light moves away, the colors fade out instantly, restarting the illusion of infinite darkness.

Everything within [[Level 10.1]]: the grass, the towering trees, the modern houses, and even the soil underfoot, exudes a strong plastic-like scent, sharp and artificial, usually likened to overheated electronics or freshly manufactured rubber. This odor is persistent and intensifies the longer an individual remains in close range to the environment. Touching or damaging these objects reveals an unsettling property: they are unnaturally destructible. Blades of grass snap with a dry, crunchy sound, shattering like thin plastic strips instead of bending or tearing. Tree bark peels off in rigid, hollow planes, showing a smooth, and perfect surface beneath, that resembles pressed polymer rather than wood. The walls of the houses, although solid and realistic in appearance, dent and crack with unnatural movements, splintering in clean breaks, as if their structure is rendered rather than built.

A strange mystery within [[Level 10.1]] surrounds a rumored entity called as '''"Stretched Eyes."''' Descriptions and alleged sightings portray it as a humanoid silhouette, but with every visible limb amd feature replaced by stretched, human-like eyes, curved and arranged to mimic the form of a person. People suggested that it move imperceptibly across the field, almost statue-like in its behavior. Witnesses occasionally describe seeing it in one location, realizing moments later that it has changed position without any clear movement, and always remaining motionless when looked directly.

The myth first gained attention when an anonymous YouTube user uploaded a grainy photo with the caption: ''"I don't know about you guys, but I stumbled upon a strange statue thingy. Isn't that terrifying to look at? (ALSO, it was found in Level 10.1.)"'' Since then, more alleged photos and reports have surfaced, and all sharing one strange similarity. '''Stretched Eyes''' always appears alone, always distant, and always staring.

<div style="margin: 10em 0;"></div>
== <Div class="b">Habitations</div> ==
{{Underline|964B00}}
=== <Div class="b">Presence of Life // Human Presence</div> ===
Human presence in [[Level 10.1]] is extremely rare, although a subtle pattern of encounters has been observed. People who remain within the level for approximately a week, based on the curcadian rythm of wanderers' (Though the passage of time is muddeled), are fairly rare with an approximately 20% chance of encountering another human during that time. These meetings are typically brief and silent, with both people often experiencing a strange sense of déjà vu or familiarity, as if the encounter is preordained or artificially staged.

Despite the lack of human activity, victims of [[Phenomenon 35|Roth Syndrome]] roam mindlessly through the sublevel. They usually exhibit distinguishable, and unnatural hues of red and amber, as if they are being infected and forcefully controlled by the environment itself.

=== <Div class="b">Brown Highlights // Community</div> ===
* About a hundred lost wanderers habit houses in the comunitty, claiming them as theirs.
* The people leading the community are '''Miller Rilly''', '''Willian Phyo''', '''Diana Aller''', three lost individuals who are currently between the age of 30 and 40.
* Miller and Willian are creative, and professional hunters, whom help keep the community clean and stable
* There are around 30 inhabited structures within community.
* People of this community can be welcome anonymous travellers, after assuring that they are not threats.
* Community is the core value of this community.
* Resources are from hostile people, and '''Wretches'''.
* Over time they have managed to greatly exapand their community.

=== <Div class="b">[[Level 10.1]] Base of [[Backroom Colonists]] // Base</div> ===
* Lost individuals, experienced wanderers and members of [[Backroom Colonists]] currently habit this base. Total population is 30 to 35 people.
* There are on average 120 days worth of supplies within this base, making it suitable for long-term residents.
* More supplies are collected from other groups and habiting places, like '''Brown Highlights''', [[M.E.G.]], etc.
* The people of this base share and care one another, making the base stable.
* Residents are researching the nature of this sublevel and report their finding to the [[M.E.G.]].

<div style="margin: 10em 0;"></div>
== <Div class="b">Entries & Exits</div> ==
{{Underline|964B00}}
=== <Div class="b">Entries</div> ===
* An underground cave located in [[Level 10]], can lead up to [[Level 10.1]].
* Digging the dirt of [[Level 10]], causes an individual to decend into [[Level 10.1]], slowly.
* Finding a modern house inside of [[Level 10]] and entering it, transitions the level to [[Level 10.1]], this transition is rapid and unstable.
* Finding a modern bridge spanning a river within [[Level 10]], then crossing it will lead to level [[Level 10.1]].

=== <Div class="b">Exits</div> ===
* Traveling far away enough from the position you enter a level you eventually you will see a barnhouse, if you enter, then when you exit you will find yourself in [[Level 10]].
* if you find a broken bridge spanning a river , crossing it will lead to level [[Level 10]].
* Digging the dirt of the sublevel, one may end up in [[Level 10.2]].

